{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"In Africa we say,"},{"time":3000,"text":"\"God gave the white man a watch"},{"time":6000,"text":"and gave the black man time.\""},{"time":8000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":12000,"text":"I think, how is it possible"},{"time":14000,"text":"for a man with so much time"},{"time":16000,"text":"to tell his story in 18 minutes?"},{"time":18000,"text":"I think it will be quite a challenge for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Most African stories these days,"},{"time":23000,"text":"they talk about famine,"},{"time":25000,"text":"HIV and AIDS,"},{"time":27000,"text":"poverty or war."},{"time":30000,"text":"But my story that I would like to share with you today"},{"time":32000,"text":"is the one about success."},{"time":35000,"text":"It is about a country"},{"time":37000,"text":"in the southwest of Africa"},{"time":40000,"text":"called Namibia."},{"time":42000,"text":"Namibia has got 2.1 million people,"},{"time":46000,"text":"but it is only twice the size of California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"I come from a region"},{"time":52000,"text":"in the remote northwest part of the country."},{"time":55000,"text":"It's called Kunene region."},{"time":57000,"text":"And in the center of Kunene region"},{"time":59000,"text":"is the village of Sesfontein. This is where I was born."},{"time":62000,"text":"This is where I'm coming from."},{"time":64000,"text":"Most people that are following the story"},{"time":66000,"text":"of Angelina Jolie"},{"time":68000,"text":"and Brad Pitt"},{"time":70000,"text":"will know where Namibia is."},{"time":73000,"text":"They love Namibia"},{"time":75000,"text":"for its beautiful dunes,"},{"time":77000,"text":"that are even taller"},{"time":79000,"text":"than the Empire State Building."},{"time":83000,"text":"Wind and time have twisted our landscape"},{"time":87000,"text":"into very strange shapes,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and these shapes are speckled with wildlife"},{"time":93000,"text":"that has become so adapted"},{"time":95000,"text":"to this harsh and strange land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"I'm a Himba."},{"time":100000,"text":"You might wonder, why are you wearing these Western clothes?"},{"time":104000,"text":"I'm a Himba and Namibian."},{"time":106000,"text":"A Himba is one of the 29"},{"time":108000,"text":"ethnic groups in Namibia."},{"time":110000,"text":"We live a very traditional lifestyle."},{"time":114000,"text":"I grew up herding,"},{"time":116000,"text":"looking after our livestock --"},{"time":118000,"text":"goats, sheep and cattle."},{"time":121000,"text":"And one day,"},{"time":124000,"text":"my father actually took me into the bush."},{"time":126000,"text":"He said, \"John,"},{"time":128000,"text":"I want you to become a good herder."},{"time":131000,"text":"Boy, if you are looking after our livestock"},{"time":134000,"text":"and you see a cheetah"},{"time":136000,"text":"eating our goat --"},{"time":138000,"text":"cheetah is very nervous --"},{"time":140000,"text":"just walk up to it."},{"time":142000,"text":"Walk up to it and smack it on the backside.\""},{"time":145000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":147000,"text":"\"And he will let go of the goat"},{"time":149000,"text":"and run off.\""},{"time":151000,"text":"But then he said,"},{"time":154000,"text":"\"Boy, if you run into a lion,"},{"time":159000,"text":"don't move."},{"time":161000,"text":"Don't move. Stand your ground."},{"time":164000,"text":"Puff up and just look it in the eye"},{"time":167000,"text":"and it may not want to fight you.\""},{"time":170000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":174000,"text":"But then, he said,"},{"time":176000,"text":"\"If you see a leopard,"},{"time":181000,"text":"boy, you better run like hell.\""},{"time":184000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":188000,"text":"\"Imagine you run faster than those goats you are looking after.\""},{"time":191000,"text":"In this way --"},{"time":193000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":196000,"text":"In this way, I actually started to learn about nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"In addition to being an ordinary Namibian"},{"time":203000,"text":"and in addition to being a Himba"},{"time":205000,"text":"I'm also a trained conservationist."},{"time":208000,"text":"And it is very important if you are in the field"},{"time":211000,"text":"to know what to confront"},{"time":213000,"text":"and what to run from."},{"time":216000,"text":"I was born in 1971."},{"time":218000,"text":"We lived under apartheid regime."},{"time":222000,"text":"The whites could farm, graze"},{"time":225000,"text":"and hunt as they wished,"},{"time":227000,"text":"but we black, we were not regarded as responsible"},{"time":230000,"text":"to use wildlife."},{"time":232000,"text":"Whenever we tried to hunt,"},{"time":234000,"text":"we were called poachers."},{"time":236000,"text":"And as a result, we were fined and locked up in jail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"Between 1966 and 1990,"},{"time":244000,"text":"the U.S. and Soviet interests"},{"time":247000,"text":"fought for control over my country."},{"time":250000,"text":"And you know, during war time,"},{"time":252000,"text":"there are militaries, armies, that are moving around."},{"time":255000,"text":"And the army hunted for valuable rhino horns"},{"time":258000,"text":"and tusks."},{"time":260000,"text":"They could sell these things for anything between"},{"time":263000,"text":"$5,000 a kilo."},{"time":265000,"text":"During the same year"},{"time":267000,"text":"almost every Himba had a rifle."},{"time":270000,"text":"Because it was wartime,"},{"time":272000,"text":"the British .303 rifle"},{"time":274000,"text":"was just all over the whole country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"Then in the same time, around 1980,"},{"time":280000,"text":"we had a very big drought."},{"time":283000,"text":"It killed almost everything that was left."},{"time":286000,"text":"Our livestock was"},{"time":288000,"text":"almost at the brink of extinction,"},{"time":290000,"text":"protected as well."},{"time":292000,"text":"We were hungry."},{"time":294000,"text":"I remember a night"},{"time":296000,"text":"when a hungry leopard"},{"time":298000,"text":"went into the house"},{"time":300000,"text":"of one of our neighbors"},{"time":302000,"text":"and took a sleeping child out of the bed."},{"time":304000,"text":"It's a very sad story."},{"time":307000,"text":"But even today,"},{"time":309000,"text":"that memory is still in people's minds."},{"time":311000,"text":"They can pinpoint the exact location"},{"time":313000,"text":"where this all happened."},{"time":316000,"text":"And then, in the same year,"},{"time":318000,"text":"we almost lost everything."},{"time":321000,"text":"And my father said, \"Why don't you just go to school?\""},{"time":325000,"text":"And they sent me off to school, just to get busy somewhere there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"And the year I went to school,"},{"time":330000,"text":"my father actually got a job with a non-governmental organization"},{"time":333000,"text":"called IRDNC, Integrated Rural Development and Nature Conservation."},{"time":337000,"text":"They actually spend a lot of time a year in the communities."},{"time":341000,"text":"They were trusted by the local communities"},{"time":344000,"text":"like our leader, Joshua Kangombe."},{"time":347000,"text":"Joshua Kangombe saw what was happening:"},{"time":349000,"text":"wildlife disappearing,"},{"time":351000,"text":"poaching was skyrocketing,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and the situation seemed very hopeless."},{"time":357000,"text":"Death and despair surrounded Joshua"},{"time":360000,"text":"and our entire communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"But then, the people from IRDNC proposed to Joshua:"},{"time":368000,"text":"What if we pay people that you trust"},{"time":372000,"text":"to look after wildlife?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Do you have anybody in your communities, or people,"},{"time":378000,"text":"that know the bush very well"},{"time":380000,"text":"and that know wildlife very well?"},{"time":383000,"text":"The headman said: \"Yes. Our poachers.\""},{"time":387000,"text":"\"Eh? The poachers?\""},{"time":389000,"text":"\"Yes. Our poachers.\""},{"time":391000,"text":"And that was my father."},{"time":394000,"text":"My father has been a poacher for quite a long time."},{"time":398000,"text":"Instead of shooting poachers dead"},{"time":401000,"text":"like they were doing elsewhere in Africa,"},{"time":404000,"text":"IRDNC has helped men reclaim their abilities"},{"time":409000,"text":"to manage their peoples"},{"time":411000,"text":"and their rights to own and manage wildlife."},{"time":415000,"text":"And thus, as people started feeling ownership over wildlife,"},{"time":419000,"text":"wildlife numbers started coming back,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and that's actually becoming a foundation for conservation in Namibia."},{"time":427000,"text":"With independence, the whole approach of community getting involved"},{"time":430000,"text":"was embraced by our new government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"Three things that actually help to build on this foundation:"},{"time":436000,"text":"The very first one is"},{"time":438000,"text":"honoring of tradition and being open to new ideas."},{"time":442000,"text":"Here is our tradition:"},{"time":444000,"text":"At every Himba village, there is a sacred fire."},{"time":448000,"text":"And at this sacred fire, the spirit of our ancestors"},{"time":451000,"text":"speak through the headman"},{"time":454000,"text":"and advise us where to get water,"},{"time":457000,"text":"where to get grazings,"},{"time":459000,"text":"and where to go and hunt."},{"time":462000,"text":"And I think this is the best way of regulating ourselves"},{"time":465000,"text":"on the environment."},{"time":468000,"text":"And here are the new ideas."},{"time":471000,"text":"Transporting rhinos using helicopters"},{"time":474000,"text":"I think is much easier"},{"time":476000,"text":"than talking through a spirit that you can't see, isn't it?"},{"time":479000,"text":"And these things we were taught by outsiders."},{"time":482000,"text":"We learned these things from outsiders."},{"time":485000,"text":"We needed new boundaries to describe our traditional lands;"},{"time":489000,"text":"we needed to learn more things like GPS"},{"time":493000,"text":"just to see whether --"},{"time":496000,"text":"can GPS really reflect the true reflection of the land"},{"time":499000,"text":"or is this just a thing made somewhere in the West?"},{"time":502000,"text":"And we then wanted to see whether we can match our"},{"time":506000,"text":"ancestral maps with digital maps made somewhere in the world."},{"time":510000,"text":"And through this,"},{"time":513000,"text":"we actually started realizing our dreams,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and we maintained honoring our traditions"},{"time":520000,"text":"but we were still open to new ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"The second element is that we wanted to have a life,"},{"time":525000,"text":"a better life where we can benefit through many things."},{"time":528000,"text":"Most poachers, like my father,"},{"time":532000,"text":"were people from our own community."},{"time":535000,"text":"They were not people from outside."},{"time":537000,"text":"These were our own people."},{"time":539000,"text":"And sometimes, once they were caught,"},{"time":542000,"text":"they were treated with respect, brought back into the communities"},{"time":545000,"text":"and they were made part of the bigger dreams."},{"time":548000,"text":"The best one, like my father -- I'm not campaigning for my father --"},{"time":551000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":553000,"text":"they were put in charge to stop others from poaching."},{"time":557000,"text":"And when this thing started going on,"},{"time":560000,"text":"we started becoming one community,"},{"time":563000,"text":"renewing our connection to nature."},{"time":565000,"text":"And that was a very strong thing in Namibia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"The last element that actually helped develop these things"},{"time":574000,"text":"was the partnerships."},{"time":576000,"text":"Our government has given legal status over our traditional lands."},{"time":581000,"text":"The other partners that we have got"},{"time":584000,"text":"is business communities."},{"time":586000,"text":"Business communities helped bring Namibia onto the world map"},{"time":591000,"text":"and they have also helped make wildlife"},{"time":594000,"text":"a very valuable land use like any other land uses"},{"time":599000,"text":"such as agriculture."},{"time":601000,"text":"And most of my conservation colleagues today"},{"time":604000,"text":"that you find in Namibia"},{"time":606000,"text":"have been trained through the initiative,"},{"time":608000,"text":"through the involvement of World Wildlife Fund"},{"time":611000,"text":"in the most up-to-date conservation practices."},{"time":614000,"text":"They have also given funding for two decades"},{"time":617000,"text":"to this whole program."},{"time":620000,"text":"And so far, with the support of World Wildlife Fund,"},{"time":623000,"text":"we've been able to scale up the very small programs"},{"time":626000,"text":"to national programs today."},{"time":628000,"text":"Namibia ... or Sesfontein"},{"time":631000,"text":"was no more an isolated village somewhere,"},{"time":634000,"text":"hidden away in Namibia."},{"time":637000,"text":"With these assets we are now part of the global village."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"Thirty years have passed"},{"time":643000,"text":"since my father's first job as a community game guard."},{"time":647000,"text":"It's very unfortunate that he passed away and he cannot see the success"},{"time":651000,"text":"as I and my children see it today."},{"time":654000,"text":"When I finished school in 1995,"},{"time":656000,"text":"there were only 20 lions in the entire Northwest -- in our area."},{"time":661000,"text":"But today, there are more than 130 lions."},{"time":667000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":673000,"text":"So please, if you go to Namibia,"},{"time":675000,"text":"make sure that you stay in the tents."},{"time":677000,"text":"Don't walk out at night!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680000,"text":"The black rhino -- they were almost extinct in 1982."},{"time":685000,"text":"But today, Kunene has the largest concentration of black rhino --"},{"time":689000,"text":"free-roaming black rhinos -- in the world."},{"time":692000,"text":"This is outside the protected area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"The leopard -- they are now in big numbers"},{"time":702000,"text":"but they are now far away from our village,"},{"time":704000,"text":"because the natural plain has multiplied,"},{"time":707000,"text":"like zebras, springboks and everything."},{"time":710000,"text":"They stay very much far away"},{"time":713000,"text":"because this other thing has multiplied"},{"time":715000,"text":"from less than a thousand to tens of thousands of animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719000,"text":"What started as very small,"},{"time":723000,"text":"community rangers getting community involved,"},{"time":726000,"text":"has now grown into something that we call conservancies."},{"time":730000,"text":"Conservancies are legally instituted institutions"},{"time":736000,"text":"by the government,"},{"time":738000,"text":"and these are run by the communities themselves, for their benefit."},{"time":741000,"text":"Today, we have got 60 conservancies"},{"time":744000,"text":"that manage and protect over 13 million hectares"},{"time":748000,"text":"of land in Namibia."},{"time":751000,"text":"We have already reshaped conservation in the entire country."},{"time":756000,"text":"Nowhere else in the world"},{"time":758000,"text":"has community-adopted conservation at this scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"In 2008, conservancy generated 5.7 million dollars."},{"time":772000,"text":"This is our new economy --"},{"time":775000,"text":"an economy based on the respect of our natural resources."},{"time":778000,"text":"And we are able to use this money for many things:"},{"time":781000,"text":"Very importantly, we put it in education."},{"time":784000,"text":"Secondly, we put it for infrastructure. Food."},{"time":787000,"text":"Very important as well -- we invest this money in AIDS and HIV education."},{"time":792000,"text":"You know that Africa is being affected by these viruses."},{"time":796000,"text":"And this is the good news from Africa"},{"time":800000,"text":"that we have to shout from the rooftops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"And now, what the world really needs"},{"time":814000,"text":"is for you to help me and our partners"},{"time":821000,"text":"take some of what we have learned in Namibia"},{"time":825000,"text":"to other places with similar problems:"},{"time":829000,"text":"places like Mongolia,"},{"time":833000,"text":"or even in your own backyards,"},{"time":837000,"text":"the Northern Great Plains,"},{"time":840000,"text":"where buffalo and other animals have suffered"},{"time":843000,"text":"and many communities are in decline."},{"time":846000,"text":"I like that one:"},{"time":849000,"text":"Namibia serving as a model to Africa,"},{"time":853000,"text":"and Africa serving as a model to the United States."},{"time":858000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":866000,"text":"We were successful in Namibia"},{"time":868000,"text":"because we dreamed of a future"},{"time":871000,"text":"that was much more than just a healthy wildlife."},{"time":876000,"text":"We knew conservation would fail"},{"time":880000,"text":"if it doesn't work to improve the lives of the local communities."},{"time":887000,"text":"So, come and talk to me about Namibia,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and better yet, come to Namibia"},{"time":895000,"text":"and see for yourself how we have done it."},{"time":897000,"text":"And please, do visit our website"},{"time":900000,"text":"to learn more and see how you can help CBNRM"},{"time":903000,"text":"in Africa and across the world."},{"time":906000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}